			<p>If there is a decimal point in a number, always use figures. For example, write 'five metres of track 'but '5.3 metres'&nbsp;</p>

			<p>Do not use an apostrophe when referring to decades or plurals as this makes them possessive: 1980s <strong>not</strong> 1980's; under-16s <strong>not</strong> under-16's</p>

